cs.MA, cs.CG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper describes a computational model inspired by slime mould that is used for data smoothing and spline curve approximation. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.MA) as the model uses a collective and distributed approach to data processing. The use of B-spline curves and their properties also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI) as relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of a biological inspiration for the model suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
